-- Plosser Says Economy May Grow 3.5% Next Year With Accelerating Inflation
-- B y   S t e v e   M a t t h e w s   a n d   K a t h l e e n   H a y s
-- 2010-12-22T17:59:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/fed-s-plosser-says-u-s-economy-to-expand-3-3-5-next-year-as-prices-gain.html
The U.S. economy is likely to expand
3 percent to 3.5 percent next year, with inflation accelerating
to as much as 2 percent, Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia
President  Charles Plosser  said.  “The economy is still in the midst of a modest recovery,”
Plosser said today in an interview on Bloomberg Radio’s “The
Hays Advantage,” with  Kathleen Hays . “My confidence that it is
sustainable is growing.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
